A witness to the Soweto tavern mass shooting says masked gunmen opened fire. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A witness to the Soweto tavern mass shooting says masked gunmen opened fire. He also says they fled in a Toyota Quantum. Fourteen people were killed just after midnight at the Nomzamo informal settlement in Orlando. READ: Death toll in Soweto tavern shooting rises to 14 Three others remain in critical condition in hospital. Gauteng police have deployed a team of detectives to the scene. Provincial police commissioner Elias Mawela said it is a bad scene. "I have no doubt in my mind that with the cooperation of the community here giving us the information, we will be able to crack this case," he said. Harrowing scenes in Soweto this morning as 14 people have been shot and killed at a tavern in Orlando. eNCA reporter Nqobile Madlala is on the scene.#DStv403